1
00:00:14,833 --> 00:00:17,167
I'm sorry, I'm a little heavy
for you.

2
00:00:17,233 --> 00:00:18,900
Are you okay?

3
00:00:18,967 --> 00:00:20,900
Red, you're wounded!

4
00:00:20,967 --> 00:00:22,667
I landed on something sharp
when we fell on the ground.

5
00:00:22,733 --> 00:00:25,433
There, the bleeding stopped.

6
00:00:25,500 --> 00:00:26,733
Don't worry.

7
00:00:26,800 --> 00:00:27,933
It will heal soon.

8
00:00:28,000 --> 00:00:30,100
- Stay here, okay?
- Yen, wait.

9
00:00:30,167 --> 00:00:31,433
You're panicking again.

10
00:00:31,500 --> 00:00:32,733
Nothing will happen to me.

11
00:00:32,800 --> 00:00:34,300
Instead of supporting
each other,

12
00:00:34,400 --> 00:00:35,333
you're getting yourself drunk.

13
00:00:35,400 --> 00:00:36,433
Victor, wait!

14
00:00:36,500 --> 00:00:38,100
This is how I cope.

15
00:00:38,167 --> 00:00:40,233
I'm still grieving!

16
00:00:40,300 --> 00:00:42,133
I want to give up
on this relationship.

17
00:00:42,200 --> 00:00:43,767
But I stayed for our son...

18
00:00:43,833 --> 00:00:44,900
for Red!

19
00:00:44,967 --> 00:00:46,267
But there's no reason for us
to stay together

20
00:00:46,333 --> 00:00:48,600
if he's not coming back anymore.

21
00:00:48,667 --> 00:00:50,100
We have to go now.

22
00:00:50,167 --> 00:00:53,100
We have to leave this shelter
and find a new one.

23
00:00:53,167 --> 00:00:54,833
Before it gets worse!

24
00:00:54,900 --> 00:00:56,233
- Let's go.
- Come on.

25
00:00:57,333 --> 00:00:59,767
You ran over Angelo.

26
00:00:59,833 --> 00:01:01,567
I will do the same thing to you.

27
00:01:01,633 --> 00:01:04,600
Go get her! People like her
shouldn't be on the road!

28
00:01:04,667 --> 00:01:06,667
And you shouldn't be released
from prison!

29
00:01:06,733 --> 00:01:07,800
You?

30
00:01:07,900 --> 00:01:10,467
This woman is not watching
where she's going.

31
00:01:10,533 --> 00:01:12,567
And now she's accusing me
of all kinds of things.

32
00:01:12,633 --> 00:01:14,133
She tried to run me over!

33
00:01:14,200 --> 00:01:16,433
She said it herself she wants
to get revenge!

34
00:01:16,500 --> 00:01:17,467
So I'm leaving.

35
00:01:17,533 --> 00:01:18,833
Ma'am, you can't leave.

36
00:01:18,900 --> 00:01:21,200
She might not file an attempted
murder case against you.

37
00:01:21,267 --> 00:01:24,633
But you were driving under
the influence of alcohol.

38
00:01:24,700 --> 00:01:26,500
And you caused an accident.

39
00:01:26,567 --> 00:01:28,667
You will go to jail!

40
00:01:28,733 --> 00:01:29,767
I'm just worried about you.

41
00:01:29,833 --> 00:01:31,233
I don't want you
to tire yourself.

42
00:01:31,300 --> 00:01:34,167
We have nothing else to do here
but rest.

43
00:01:34,233 --> 00:01:35,400
Don't worry.

44
00:01:36,933 --> 00:01:38,267
There's a snake!

45
00:01:38,333 --> 00:01:40,900
Eden, there really is a snake!
Please, wake up!

46
00:01:53,633 --> 00:01:54,867
Yen...

47
00:01:54,933 --> 00:01:56,267
What are we going to do?

48
00:01:56,333 --> 00:01:58,200
Don't move! Stay still.

49
00:01:58,267 --> 00:01:59,267
Don't move.

50
00:02:01,433 --> 00:02:03,000
The snake will bite us
if you move.

51
00:02:03,067 --> 00:02:04,967
What are we going to do, Red?

52
00:02:05,033 --> 00:02:10,933
When I say run, you run.

53
00:02:11,000 --> 00:02:12,200
Okay?

54
00:02:12,267 --> 00:02:13,267
I don't want to!

55
00:02:13,333 --> 00:02:14,533
I'm going to distract the snake.

56
00:02:14,633 --> 00:02:15,600
Save yourself!

57
00:02:15,667 --> 00:02:18,000
What? Are you going to use
yourself as bait?

58
00:02:22,333 --> 00:02:24,500
I'm sorry, the subscriber
cannot be reached.

59
00:02:24,567 --> 00:02:26,600
Please try again later.

60
00:02:35,467 --> 00:02:36,933
Hello, Attorney.

61
00:02:37,000 --> 00:02:38,500
What made you call?

62
00:02:38,567 --> 00:02:40,767
Your wife is in the west
precinct.

63
00:02:40,833 --> 00:02:43,867
She's there for driving
under the influence of alcohol

64
00:02:43,933 --> 00:02:45,933
and physical injuries.

65
00:02:46,000 --> 00:02:48,267
What? What happened?

66
00:02:48,367 --> 00:02:49,833
Did she get in an accident?

67
00:02:49,900 --> 00:02:51,533
Is she all right?

68
00:02:51,600 --> 00:02:54,400
She's fine.

69
00:02:54,467 --> 00:02:56,467
The victim isn't seriously hurt.

70
00:02:56,533 --> 00:02:57,833
But it's stated here that
the victim is the woman

71
00:02:57,900 --> 00:02:59,533
we put in jail before.

72
00:02:59,600 --> 00:03:01,067
Amanda Sta. Maria.

73
00:03:01,133 --> 00:03:02,500
My God!

74
00:03:02,567 --> 00:03:03,600
Don't worry, Victor.

75
00:03:03,667 --> 00:03:05,767
We'll fix this.

76
00:03:05,833 --> 00:03:08,733
But it's too late to bail her
out now.

77
00:03:08,800 --> 00:03:11,033
She won't be able to get out
until tomorrow.

78
00:03:11,100 --> 00:03:15,333
Attorney, if she has to spend
the night in jail

79
00:03:15,400 --> 00:03:18,033
to learn her lesson, so be it!

80
00:03:19,433 --> 00:03:20,833
Thank you for your help.

81
00:03:56,567 --> 00:03:58,200
Stop worrying about me!

82
00:03:58,267 --> 00:04:00,667
Just do as I say.

83
00:04:00,733 --> 00:04:02,100
Yen, please, you have to run!

84
00:04:02,167 --> 00:04:03,967
- Go!
- I won't leave you here!

85
00:04:04,033 --> 00:04:06,567
Yen, if you don't run now,
we'll both die!

86
00:04:08,900 --> 00:04:10,133
Yen, come on.

87
00:04:13,667 --> 00:04:15,833
What are you doing?

88
00:04:15,900 --> 00:04:17,100
Yen, what are...

89
00:04:19,900 --> 00:04:21,000
Yen!

90
00:04:21,067 --> 00:04:22,900
Yen, no!

91
00:04:22,967 --> 00:04:24,367
Yen, stop!

92
00:04:32,600 --> 00:04:34,233
Okay, keep distracting it.

93
00:04:37,933 --> 00:04:39,400
- Red! Hurry!
- Let's go!

94
00:04:45,467 --> 00:04:47,133
You were great!

95
00:04:47,200 --> 00:04:48,800
You beat a snake!

96
00:04:48,867 --> 00:04:50,167
You just swing your knife
around like this!

97
00:04:50,233 --> 00:04:52,000
Left, right, left, right!

98
00:04:52,067 --> 00:04:54,200
The snake was startled.

99
00:04:54,267 --> 00:04:57,833
But you came up with the idea
to get out of that cave.

100
00:04:57,900 --> 00:04:59,767
We both did.

101
00:04:59,833 --> 00:05:02,167
Teamwork makes the dream work,
right?

102
00:05:02,267 --> 00:05:04,167
We just got lucky.

103
00:05:04,233 --> 00:05:07,367
We're fortunate
to be still alive.

104
00:05:07,433 --> 00:05:10,700
That's why we have to celebrate.

105
00:05:10,767 --> 00:05:15,600
Only a few people can say that
they survived a snake attack.

106
00:05:15,667 --> 00:05:19,633
We have to think about our plans
for tomorrow.

107
00:05:19,700 --> 00:05:22,567
Looks like this place is safe
enough for us to stay the night.

108
00:05:23,600 --> 00:05:25,633
We can sleep on the sand
for now.

109
00:05:27,633 --> 00:05:30,267
And then we'll make a shelter
tomorrow.

110
00:05:54,833 --> 00:05:57,067
There you go. This thing calls
for a celebration.

111
00:05:57,133 --> 00:05:58,567
Good job, Partner!

112
00:06:00,333 --> 00:06:01,700
Do this side next.

113
00:06:03,167 --> 00:06:05,167
Here, I have an idea.

114
00:06:39,733 --> 00:06:41,800
What do you think?

115
00:06:41,900 --> 00:06:43,533
Red, look at what I did.

116
00:06:48,400 --> 00:06:50,400
Hey, are you okay?

117
00:06:50,467 --> 00:06:52,367
You've been quiet.

118
00:06:52,433 --> 00:06:53,900
I'm okay.

119
00:06:53,967 --> 00:06:56,500
I'm a little thirsty.

120
00:06:56,567 --> 00:06:57,967
You need water.

121
00:06:58,033 --> 00:06:59,233
Wait.

122
00:07:07,133 --> 00:07:08,300
Here.

123
00:07:08,367 --> 00:07:09,733
Thank you.

124
00:07:14,433 --> 00:07:15,700
Wait, let's change your bandage.

125
00:07:15,767 --> 00:07:16,967
No! No need!

126
00:07:17,033 --> 00:07:19,567
I checked the wound earlier,
and it's starting to dry out.

127
00:07:19,633 --> 00:07:22,600
It might bleed again
if we expose it.

128
00:07:22,667 --> 00:07:24,333
- I'm okay.
- Are you sure?

129
00:07:28,300 --> 00:07:29,633
Did you see our shelter?

130
00:07:29,700 --> 00:07:32,600
It looks good! We won't have
to worry at night.

131
00:07:32,667 --> 00:07:34,100
Come on, hurry!

132
00:07:47,933 --> 00:07:49,267
Victor!

133
00:07:51,367 --> 00:07:52,967
Where's our lawyer?

134
00:07:53,033 --> 00:07:55,233
I want that attorney fired!

135
00:07:55,300 --> 00:07:57,033
He left me here overnight!

136
00:07:57,100 --> 00:07:58,300
Rina, can you please
keep it down?

137
00:07:58,367 --> 00:07:59,467
Keep it down? Why?

138
00:07:59,533 --> 00:08:00,867
Are they going to file
a complaint? And then what?

139
00:08:00,933 --> 00:08:02,533
They'll put me in jail again?

140
00:08:03,567 --> 00:08:06,300
Why didn't you call our friends?

141
00:08:06,367 --> 00:08:08,667
I shouldn't have stayed
overnight here!

142
00:08:08,733 --> 00:08:09,733
No!

143
00:08:09,800 --> 00:08:12,233
It was my decision to keep you
here overnight.

144
00:08:14,567 --> 00:08:15,733
How dare you!

145
00:08:16,833 --> 00:08:19,667
Because you needed to learn
your lesson.

146
00:08:19,733 --> 00:08:22,200
For you to realize that
what you're doing is wrong.

147
00:08:22,300 --> 00:08:24,433
Leave Amanda alone.

148
00:08:27,167 --> 00:08:28,767
And then what?
I'll just let her win?

149
00:08:28,833 --> 00:08:30,100
Is that what you want, Victor?

150
00:08:30,167 --> 00:08:31,633
I can't let that happen!

151
00:08:31,700 --> 00:08:33,500
She's a monster!

152
00:08:43,933 --> 00:08:47,833
I'm sure many fruits fell
because of the storm last night.

153
00:08:47,900 --> 00:08:49,900
I hope we can find something
to eat.

154
00:08:54,600 --> 00:08:57,333
Red, why don't you go back
to our shelter?

155
00:08:57,400 --> 00:08:59,400
I can do this on my own.

156
00:08:59,467 --> 00:09:01,933
There might be a spider
out here.

157
00:09:02,000 --> 00:09:03,667
Red.

158
00:09:03,733 --> 00:09:06,567
Go on. I'm going to be slow,
but I'll be right behind you.

159
00:09:06,633 --> 00:09:08,267
Just call if you need me.

160
00:09:08,333 --> 00:09:09,367
I'll be here.

161
00:09:09,433 --> 00:09:11,200
Are you sure?

162
00:09:12,533 --> 00:09:14,767
Just keep talking
so I can hear you.

163
00:09:22,200 --> 00:09:25,033
Red, are you okay?

164
00:09:25,100 --> 00:09:26,233
I'm good.

165
00:09:26,300 --> 00:09:27,300
Are you okay?

166
00:09:27,400 --> 00:09:28,700
Of course.

167
00:09:28,767 --> 00:09:32,133
Be careful around tree branches.

168
00:09:55,167 --> 00:09:57,833
Red, there are some fruits here!

169
00:09:57,900 --> 00:09:59,800
Yen, be careful.
It could be poisonous.

170
00:09:59,867 --> 00:10:01,467
No, the ants are trying
to get it.

171
00:10:01,567 --> 00:10:05,067
So that means it's not
poisonous.

172
00:10:07,200 --> 00:10:09,267
And it smells sweet.

173
00:10:14,400 --> 00:10:17,033
Red, I think we can eat this.

174
00:10:17,100 --> 00:10:18,533
Come on.

175
00:10:21,967 --> 00:10:24,300
Hey, are you okay?

176
00:10:26,067 --> 00:10:29,467
I was looking at something.

177
00:10:32,733 --> 00:10:34,800
Are you sure?

178
00:10:34,900 --> 00:10:37,100
Red, you're burning up.

179
00:10:40,567 --> 00:10:42,533
- No.
- Red!

180
00:10:43,867 --> 00:10:46,100
Do you feel sick?

181
00:10:46,167 --> 00:10:47,133
- No.
- Red!

182
00:10:47,200 --> 00:10:49,500
I think you have a fever.

183
00:10:49,567 --> 00:10:51,000
I'm okay.

184
00:10:51,067 --> 00:10:55,700
We got wet in the rain,
and we were also sweaty.

185
00:10:55,767 --> 00:10:57,167
So I feel a little sick.

186
00:10:57,233 --> 00:10:59,933
But I just need to get
some rest. I'll be okay.

187
00:11:00,000 --> 00:11:02,300
Let me see your wound.

188
00:11:02,367 --> 00:11:03,967
No, no, no.

189
00:11:04,033 --> 00:11:05,200
I just checked it.

190
00:11:05,267 --> 00:11:06,267
It's okay.

191
00:11:06,333 --> 00:11:08,767
I'm good. I just need some rest.

192
00:11:08,867 --> 00:11:11,567
Okay. Eat this first, and then
we'll return to our shelter.

193
00:11:11,633 --> 00:11:14,167
So you can rest. Okay?

194
00:11:14,233 --> 00:11:15,667
Thank you.

195
00:11:36,800 --> 00:11:41,367
Rina posted bail today.

196
00:11:41,467 --> 00:11:42,867
Wait. She's out already?

197
00:11:42,933 --> 00:11:45,733
That was fast.

198
00:11:45,800 --> 00:11:48,267
I don't expect her to stay
in jail for a long time.

199
00:11:48,333 --> 00:11:49,933
They have money.

200
00:11:51,567 --> 00:11:54,933
You should have filed
an attempted murder case

201
00:11:55,000 --> 00:11:56,533
against that woman.

202
00:11:56,600 --> 00:12:00,367
So she won't be able to bail
herself out.

203
00:12:00,433 --> 00:12:01,833
That's impossible to happen.

204
00:12:01,900 --> 00:12:04,133
It's enough that
I let that woman know

205
00:12:04,200 --> 00:12:08,233
that I won't back down.

206
00:12:08,300 --> 00:12:10,633
I hope she'll leave you alone.

207
00:12:10,700 --> 00:12:12,800
She seems out of her mind.

208
00:12:12,867 --> 00:12:16,500
She's acting like crazy.
She might try to harm us again.

209
00:12:16,600 --> 00:12:20,900
I'm not scared of Rina.

210
00:12:20,967 --> 00:12:25,200
But I'm worried about Yenyen.

211
00:12:25,267 --> 00:12:28,833
I just want to focus
on finding my daughter.

212
00:12:36,600 --> 00:12:38,833
It's cold.

213
00:12:38,900 --> 00:12:44,867
Stop complaining. This will help
to get your fever down.

214
00:12:44,933 --> 00:12:46,467
It's good. I'm okay.

215
00:12:46,533 --> 00:12:48,067
Please, stop.

216
00:12:48,167 --> 00:12:49,733
Red.

217
00:12:49,800 --> 00:12:53,367
Didn't you tell me to trust you?

218
00:12:53,433 --> 00:12:56,800
This time I want you
to trust me, okay?

219
00:12:59,667 --> 00:13:01,000
Just rest for now.

220
00:13:06,567 --> 00:13:08,200
Let me change your bandage.

221
00:13:08,267 --> 00:13:09,367
No need.

222
00:13:09,433 --> 00:13:10,367
Don't worry about that, please.

223
00:13:10,433 --> 00:13:12,533
Why are you trying to hide it
from me?

224
00:13:12,600 --> 00:13:13,967
- Don't touch it.
- Let me see it.

225
00:13:14,033 --> 00:13:14,967
- No.
- Come on, please.

226
00:13:15,033 --> 00:13:16,167
- Let me see it.
- Stop, Yenyen.

227
00:13:16,233 --> 00:13:17,600
Let me see.

228
00:13:28,500 --> 00:13:30,600
Red!

229
00:13:30,667 --> 00:13:32,300
Your wound!

230
00:13:46,767 --> 00:13:50,667
Don't tell me you're going
to lecture me again.

231
00:13:54,967 --> 00:13:56,933
I'm not your enemy here, Rina.

232
00:13:58,800 --> 00:14:03,500
If I have said something
these past few days...

233
00:14:03,567 --> 00:14:07,667
and for letting you spend
the night in jail.

234
00:14:07,733 --> 00:14:08,933
I'm sorry.

235
00:14:10,967 --> 00:14:12,400
Please forgive me.

236
00:14:17,667 --> 00:14:20,000
I'm just frustrated
with our situation.

237
00:14:20,067 --> 00:14:22,067
I'm having a hard time too.

238
00:14:24,300 --> 00:14:26,433
And, of course,

239
00:14:26,500 --> 00:14:29,233
I'm also not happy that
the woman who murdered our son

240
00:14:29,333 --> 00:14:30,800
was released from prison.

241
00:14:33,133 --> 00:14:36,467
But I'm putting that aside
for now.

242
00:14:36,533 --> 00:14:38,800
Because I want to focus on Red.

243
00:14:41,833 --> 00:14:46,267
Hon, I can't worry about you,
too,

244
00:14:46,333 --> 00:14:47,767
and whatever you're doing...

245
00:14:49,500 --> 00:14:52,200
while we're still looking
for Red.

246
00:14:52,267 --> 00:14:53,933
I hope you understand that.

247
00:14:56,833 --> 00:14:57,933
I'm sorry.

248
00:14:59,600 --> 00:15:01,067
I promise...

249
00:15:02,800 --> 00:15:05,367
I won't put myself
in harm's way again.

250
00:15:19,633 --> 00:15:22,467
I was so worried when
the attorney called me.

251
00:15:23,867 --> 00:15:25,733
What if something happens to you
while you're there?

252
00:15:28,167 --> 00:15:31,767
What if you end up getting hurt
instead of Amanda?

253
00:15:33,667 --> 00:15:38,233
Like I said, I promise
I won't do that again.

254
00:15:38,333 --> 00:15:39,933
I'm sorry.

255
00:15:44,433 --> 00:15:47,267
I'm looking forward to seeing
our son again.

256
00:15:49,700 --> 00:15:52,833
I cannot be behind bars
when he gets back.

257
00:15:59,400 --> 00:16:01,900
Red, why didn't you tell me
about this?

258
00:16:05,767 --> 00:16:08,533
I don't want you to worry
about me.

259
00:16:08,633 --> 00:16:15,033
I don't want you to blame
yourself.

260
00:16:15,100 --> 00:16:18,867
So you're just going to hide
this from me?

261
00:16:18,933 --> 00:16:20,367
Until when?

262
00:16:20,433 --> 00:16:21,967
Until it gets infected?

263
00:16:24,867 --> 00:16:26,567
Red, I thought we were partners.

264
00:16:28,400 --> 00:16:31,200
We shouldn't hide things
from each other.

265
00:16:34,467 --> 00:16:37,133
Sorry for being weak
and a crybaby.

266
00:16:38,167 --> 00:16:41,600
Probably that's why you don't
want to tell me the truth.

267
00:16:46,800 --> 00:16:48,833
Let's stop blaming each other.

268
00:16:48,900 --> 00:16:51,200
I think I'm getting better.

269
00:16:51,267 --> 00:16:55,133
It's probably from the sponge
bath you gave me.

270
00:16:55,200 --> 00:16:57,033
Let's get some rest.

271
00:16:57,100 --> 00:16:59,000
I'll be fine tomorrow.

272
00:17:00,033 --> 00:17:01,367
Red.

273
00:17:01,433 --> 00:17:03,033
You should get some rest too.

274
00:17:03,100 --> 00:17:06,367
You must be tired
from taking care of me.

275
00:17:30,200 --> 00:17:33,167
Red.

276
00:17:33,233 --> 00:17:34,700
Red, are you okay?

277
00:17:37,067 --> 00:17:38,133
Red?

278
00:17:58,333 --> 00:18:00,267
Red, sorry we don't have a fire.

279
00:18:02,433 --> 00:18:05,300
Even if I try to start one,
it might not work.

280
00:18:06,767 --> 00:18:07,733
I'll just lay down with you,
okay?

281
00:18:07,800 --> 00:18:11,600
I hope you won't feel awkward.

282
00:18:11,667 --> 00:18:13,300
You need body heat.

283
00:18:23,100 --> 00:18:30,033
Red, I know you're having
a hard time right now.

284
00:18:30,100 --> 00:18:37,067
When I was young,
my mom would tell me stories

285
00:18:37,133 --> 00:18:38,633
whenever I was sick.

286
00:18:41,267 --> 00:18:44,633
So that I could forget
about my pain.

287
00:18:47,133 --> 00:18:49,200
Do you want me to tell you
stories?

288
00:18:57,700 --> 00:19:02,200
I remember when we first
got here on this island.

289
00:19:02,267 --> 00:19:05,567
Help! Help!

290
00:19:05,633 --> 00:19:06,733
Miss...

291
00:19:08,667 --> 00:19:10,100
Miss, hold on to me!

292
00:19:10,167 --> 00:19:12,200
Hold on to me!

293
00:19:12,267 --> 00:19:13,633
Come on.

294
00:19:16,033 --> 00:19:17,200
Thank you! Thank you.

295
00:19:17,267 --> 00:19:20,300
I thought I was the only one
who survived the crash.

296
00:19:20,367 --> 00:19:21,700
Are you okay?

297
00:19:21,767 --> 00:19:24,200
Yeah, I'm good.

298
00:19:24,267 --> 00:19:25,633
You look familiar.

299
00:19:25,700 --> 00:19:28,333
You were the guy
from the campus.

300
00:19:28,400 --> 00:19:29,933
By the way, I'm Red.

301
00:19:32,200 --> 00:19:34,867
We were often bickering.

302
00:19:34,933 --> 00:19:37,367
Look! It's not working anymore!

303
00:19:37,433 --> 00:19:39,033
It's your fault!

304
00:19:39,100 --> 00:19:41,000
- Why are you blaming me?
- You wasted it!

305
00:19:44,133 --> 00:19:48,933
If we can find a reason
to laugh, why deprive ourselves?

306
00:19:49,000 --> 00:19:51,733
Sorry, but your jokes
are not helping.

307
00:19:51,800 --> 00:19:54,067
What are you doing?
I don't know how you can take

308
00:19:54,133 --> 00:19:55,433
our situation so lightly.

309
00:19:55,500 --> 00:19:57,700
I'm not taking things lightly.

310
00:19:57,767 --> 00:19:59,167
I'm just trying to make it
bearable.

311
00:19:59,233 --> 00:20:00,300
I was just trying...

312
00:20:02,100 --> 00:20:03,400
Never mind.

313
00:20:05,233 --> 00:20:07,533
You're always kidding around.

314
00:20:07,600 --> 00:20:09,567
And I'm too serious.

315
00:20:14,600 --> 00:20:16,567
We're both athletes, right?

316
00:20:19,433 --> 00:20:22,633
But we know nothing
about teamwork.

317
00:20:22,700 --> 00:20:25,800
But when Coach Vinluan got here,

318
00:20:28,033 --> 00:20:30,267
she taught us to work together.

319
00:20:30,333 --> 00:20:33,900
I can't imagine what could
have happened to us without her.

320
00:20:33,967 --> 00:20:37,300
I don't know how we could work
together.

321
00:20:37,400 --> 00:20:39,867
Very good. Very good.

322
00:20:41,100 --> 00:20:43,167
You did great.

323
00:20:43,233 --> 00:20:46,467
Coach, drink some water.

324
00:20:57,600 --> 00:20:59,267
But when we lost her...

325
00:21:00,933 --> 00:21:04,633
when she died, I thought
I would give up.

326
00:21:13,800 --> 00:21:16,000
But you never gave up.

327
00:21:17,233 --> 00:21:19,333
You never gave up on us, Red.

328
00:21:21,267 --> 00:21:24,200
Yen, stop.

329
00:21:24,267 --> 00:21:26,400
Yen, she's gone. Please stop.

330
00:21:26,467 --> 00:21:28,367
Yen. Yen, stop.

331
00:21:29,700 --> 00:21:31,033
Perhaps you're right.

332
00:21:31,100 --> 00:21:33,200
We might have a slim chance.

333
00:21:33,267 --> 00:21:35,933
But no matter how small
the chance we get,

334
00:21:36,000 --> 00:21:38,400
I will never give up.

335
00:21:38,467 --> 00:21:40,200
I will keep fighting.

336
00:21:40,267 --> 00:21:43,767
Hopelessness is our enemy here.

337
00:21:43,867 --> 00:21:46,467
Don't let it beat us.

338
00:21:46,533 --> 00:21:47,500
Are you okay?

339
00:21:52,633 --> 00:21:53,633
I'm okay.

340
00:22:02,667 --> 00:22:03,600
Yen!

341
00:22:03,667 --> 00:22:05,000
I thought...

342
00:22:32,033 --> 00:22:33,167
Red...

343
00:22:33,233 --> 00:22:35,767
Red, you gave me courage.

344
00:22:35,833 --> 00:22:38,067
You gave me courage, Red.

345
00:22:44,700 --> 00:22:47,300
We'll keep fighting, okay?

346
00:22:47,367 --> 00:22:49,133
We'll never give up.

347
00:22:51,167 --> 00:22:52,567
We'll keep fighting.

348
00:22:57,233 --> 00:23:03,267
I promise I'll look
for medicine tomorrow.

349
00:23:03,333 --> 00:23:06,467
You'll get better.

350
00:23:06,533 --> 00:23:07,467
You'll get through this, Red.

351
00:23:07,533 --> 00:23:09,000
Okay?

352
00:23:21,500 --> 00:23:22,600
Where are you going?

353
00:23:22,667 --> 00:23:23,900
To Rina.

354
00:23:23,967 --> 00:23:25,700
I know she paid your landlord
off!

355
00:23:25,767 --> 00:23:27,167
That's why she kicked us out.

356
00:23:27,233 --> 00:23:28,833
What if she has nothing
to do with it?

357
00:23:28,900 --> 00:23:30,133
It will be nothing but trouble.

358
00:23:30,200 --> 00:23:32,033
So are we just going to let her
trample on us?

359
00:23:32,100 --> 00:23:34,100
Just like the time when
she put me in jail!

360
00:23:34,167 --> 00:23:35,300
How are you?

361
00:23:35,367 --> 00:23:37,400
Looks like you're having
a good day.

362
00:23:37,467 --> 00:23:40,933
I woke up with renewed energy...

363
00:23:41,000 --> 00:23:42,567
to look for our son.

364
00:23:42,633 --> 00:23:44,833
Red, there's medicine
in that bag!

365
00:23:44,900 --> 00:23:46,633
- Stay here, okay?
- Yen, stay here.

366
00:23:46,700 --> 00:23:49,400
Red, you should be awake
when I get back, okay?

367
00:23:49,467 --> 00:23:51,967
Someone's waiting for you, Yen.

368
00:23:52,033 --> 00:23:53,867
You have to get through this.

369
00:23:56,667 --> 00:23:58,367
You can do this, Eden!

370
00:23:58,433 --> 00:24:00,433
Never give up!
